Adjust rack to top position and preheat broiler to high (or oven to 500 degrees). Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}(leaves and stems, keeping them separate). Deseed and finely dice @jalapeño{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Drain @black beans{13.4%ounce}, reserving liquid in a small #bowl{}.

In a medium bowl, combine tomato, cilantro leaves, half the jalapeño, juice from 2 lime wedges (4 wedges for 4 servings), and 2 TBSP onion (3 TBSP for 4 servings); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. In a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and lime zest (to taste). Stir in water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add beans, @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon}, and cilantro stems. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and thoroughly combined, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add bean liquid and a pinch of salt. Cook until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; mash beans until mostly smooth.

Meanwhile, drain @corn{13.4%ounce} and pat dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add corn and cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, about ~{4%minutes}. Add 1 TBSP @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Continue to cook, stirring, until browned all over, about ~{1%minute} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a second medium bowl.

Place @flour tortillas{6} on a #baking sheet{}. Drizzle on both sides with @olive oil{2%tablespoon}; rub all over to coat. Poke all over with a #fork{}. Broil, flipping halfway through, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Tortillas brown quickly! Keep a close eye on them.

Spread tortillas with beans. Evenly top with @Mexican cheese blend{½%cup}, corn, salsa, crema, and remaining jalapeño (to taste). Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.